# Cloudflare Pages may 302 /page.html → /page (“pretty URLs”). That breaks auth ?return= which
# expects real paths like /locker.html. These 301s send extensionless URLs back to the .html file
# so the final address bar (and pathname) match our static file names. Query strings are preserved
# by the client redirect chain per Pages behavior.
#
# Login: do NOT add /login → /login.html 301. Pages “pretty URLs” can also redirect /login.html → /login,
# which ping-pongs with our rule and causes ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS on /login.html.
# Use /login.html only in links (no redirect rules for /login).
# Admin: no /admin → /admin.html 301 here (same Pages ping-pong risk as login). Use /admin.html in links.
# pilot-auth normalizes extensionless paths in ?return= (lantern-pilot-auth.js).
#
# Locker, store, games — legacy three-line pattern (review separately if needed):
# - /page/ → /page (301)
# - /page.html → /page (301)
# - /page → /page.html (200)

# Root: serve index.html (client redirects to /login.html). Do NOT rewrite / → login.html.

/locker/ /locker 301
/locker.html /locker 301
/locker /locker.html 200

/store/ /store 301
/store.html /store 301
/store /store.html 200

/games/ /games 301
/games.html /games 301
/games /games.html 200

/teacher /teacher.html 301
/explore /explore.html 301
# change-password: no /change-password → .html 301 (same Pages ping-pong risk). Use /change-password.html in links.
